article.headline: Tulsa 63, Hawaii 55
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Jillian Robbins scored 22 points and Emily
Jaskowiak added 15 to lead Tulsa over Hawaii 63-55 Saturday night.

The Rainbow Wahine (5-13, 3-6 Western Athletic Conference) shot
46 percent (12-of-26) and the Golden Hurricane shot 39 percent
(11-of-28) to stand tied 31-31 at halftime.

Tulsa (13-6, 6-3) remained steady in the second half, making
nine of 28 shots from the field (32 percent), while Hawaii cooled
off, hitting just nine of 31 shots (29 percent).

Meanwhile, the Golden Hurricane scored 22 points on 28 free
throws, while Hawaii was 9-of-11 from the foul line.

Jaskowiak grabbed a game-high 13 rebounds.

April Atuaia led Hawaii with 13 points. Jade Abele had 11 for
the Rainbow Wahine and Janevia Taylor added 10.
